		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Haste, double attack, and IoN proc<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Feb 6th 1:35 PM2002 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=10130205503990&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=10130205503990&num=2&post=1&replyto=10130205503990"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=10130205503990></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=83710"><span id=Scholar>jcasetnl</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>153 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.35]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=jcasetnl&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I recently sold my FRSS and turned the money around into getting an FBSS.&nbsp;&nbsp;So now I have a few questions about haste and I want to understand a &quot;complete&quot; dmg/dly ratio for my character.<br><br>First of all, I want to make sure I understand delay reduction correctly.  I think this is the basic equation:<br><br>DLY - [(DLY * Haste%)/2] = new DLY<br><br>So let's take the FBSS and Centi Warspear as an example where DLY = 30 and Haste% is 21:<br><br>30 - [(30 * .21) / 2] = <br><br>30 - 3.15 = 26.85 <br><br>So my new delay is 26.85 (btw, is this figure rounded off in actual game play?)<br><br>Next I was wondering if haste affects double attack.  For simplicities sake, let's say my chance of double attack is 50%, meaning on average I'll double attack every other swing.  <br><br>This is where I get really confused but without haste, would this mean that my actual &quot;damage ratio&quot; is 30dmg 30dly with the Centi warspear?  In other words:<br><br>NormalDMG + (DA% * NormalDMG) = Total Dmg  <br><br>20dmg + (.5 * 20) = Total Dmg<br><br>20dmg + 10 = 30<br><br>So my total dmg after double attack (without haste) would be 30.  My delay is also 30, so my ratio is 1/1 for dmg/dly.  Is that right?  (btw, I'm assuming for ratio the delay is divided by the damage (i.e. 30/20 = 1.5) <br><br>Next, what happens when I figure haste in?  Is my dmg/dly ratio now 30/26.85?  So is my new ratio 0.895?  <br><br>Lastly let's consider the IoN proc.  I believe on a 2h weapon at 100dex, there is a 5% chance of proc'ing.  Now since there's no simple way to factor this into the dmg/dly ratio (that I can think of), let's consider how dmg/dly would affect the number of times you proc.  Unfortunately there's a number of variables here.  For example, if you proc more, the fights are shorter, and therefore you swing less.  Also the proc might be partially or completely resisted.  But to keep things simple I'll take the 5% base value and see how haste affects it:<br><br>In that case,<br><br>[(nonhasteddly - hasteddly)/ nonhasteddly] + 1 * procrate = newprocrate<br><br>or<br><br>[(30 - 26.85)/30] + 1 *.05 = 0.05525<br><br><br>So in a nutshell what I'm getting at is that your proc will go off roughly 10% more overall because of your haste, which only makes sense the dmg reduction of the FBSS is roughly 10%: <br><br>(0.05525 - .05)/.05 = .105<br><br><br>And I'm spent.<br><br><br><br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >2 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Feb 6th 10:25 PM2002 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=10130205503990&num=2&post=1&replyto=101304860464847"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=101304860464847></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=38412"><span id=Scholar>Dalantia</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>272 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.24]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Dalantia&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Simply because I don't like having to crunch obscene amounts of numbers to see how new gear will affect me, I have a simple philosophy:<br><br>If it keeps me from getting beat on, me like.<br><br>If it hits really hard, me like.<br><br>If it makes me swing more, me like.<br><br>*shrug*<br><br>And as for affecting double attack, one would think the roll for the skill working would be the same on every single swing.&nbsp;&nbsp;So you're swinging a 20/30 weapon MAYBE twice a round, and when you hit for max damage on both hits, then it can be a really big hit, but if you miss twice, then.  *shrug*<br><br>I realize I'm stating the obvious, but I don't think double attack should be worried about when you're dealing with haste.  Just treat your weapon as if it would only swing once (Because you may have a string of bad luck and see your Double Attack work maybe once in a fight) and I think you'd do fine.  *shrug*<br><br>As for equations, I may be good at math, but all these give me a headache, and I'm not afraid to admit it.<br><br>For the record, I'm working on gaining a haste item, but my Mith and my Centi Warspear are fast enough for now, and I'm a cheap pally; right now, I'm saving up for better armor.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Feb  6 21:25:49 2002</em></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Dalantia Dragonfury<br>Crusader of the Burning Heart, 60th Protection, Third Blessing<br>Fennin Ro<br>New Dawnings<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60479" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=604